# Database Schema Structure

This guide outlines where database schema is defined and what files need to be updated when making schema changes.

## Type Definitions

The Supabase database types are defined in [types/supabase.ts](mdc:types/supabase.ts). When adding or modifying tables or columns, this file should be updated first to ensure type safety throughout the application.

Example of a table definition:
```typescript
escapes_data: {
  Row: {
    country: string;
    created_at: string;
    id: number;
    image: string;
    link: string;
    price: string;
    subtitle: string;
    title: string;
    type: "hotel" | "flight" | "hotel+flight";
    validFrom: string | null;
    validTo: string | null;
  };
  // Insert and Update definitions...
}
```

## Data Access Layer

The data fetching logic that interacts with the database is contained in:

- [app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts](mdc:app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts) - Server actions for fetching escape data

When adding new fields or tables, ensure corresponding EscapeData type is updated here:

```typescript
export type EscapeData = {
  id: number;
  created_at: string;
  // ... other fields
  type: "hotel" | "flight" | "hotel+flight" | null;
  // ... 
};
```

## Form Components

Form components that create or update database records need to be updated when schema changes:

- [app/admin/escapes/components/EscapeForm.tsx](mdc:app/admin/escapes/components/EscapeForm.tsx) - Form component for creating/editing escapes
- [app/admin/escapes/actions.ts](mdc:app/admin/escapes/actions.ts) - Server actions for creating/updating escapes

Important patterns to update in actions.ts:
1. Form schema validation (using Zod)
2. Data transformation between form and database
3. Error handling

```typescript
// Example of schema validation
const escapeFormSchema = z.object({
  // ... other fields
  type: dealTypeEnum, // z.enum(["hotel", "flight", "hotel+flight"]),
  // ...
});
```

## Display Components

Components that display database content need updates when schema changes:

- [components/escapes/EscapeCard.tsx](mdc:components/escapes/EscapeCard.tsx) - Card component showing escape details
- [components/escapes/EscapeGrid.tsx](mdc:components/escapes/EscapeGrid.tsx) - Grid container for escape cards

## Schema Change Checklist

When modifying the database schema:

1. Update Supabase type definitions in [types/supabase.ts](mdc:types/supabase.ts)
2. Update EscapeData type in [app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts](mdc:app/actions/fetchEscapes.ts)
3. Update form validation in [app/admin/escapes/actions.ts](mdc:app/admin/escapes/actions.ts)
4. Update form components in [app/admin/escapes/components/EscapeForm.tsx](mdc:app/admin/escapes/components/EscapeForm.tsx)
5. Update display components like [components/escapes/EscapeCard.tsx](mdc:components/escapes/EscapeCard.tsx)
6. Test form submission and display with the new schema